						               													<description>Space, 2120. FLT was discovered decades ago, along with a surprising number of inhabited worlds. Now, in regions throughout the galaxy, the search is on for mineral-rich asteroids. In Spacemaster 2120 your small mining craft will explore the 24 sectors of SR-227 and collect six types of minerals. Planets in the sector have different demands for these minerals, so to turn a profit you must plan your movements carefully and act accordingly. You&amp;rsquo;ll also have to convince the inhabitants to trade with you &amp;ndash; or use force to convince them. Fuel is no longer an issue, but you&amp;rsquo;ll have to visit Earth for the turbo variety or convert some Uraninite. Other minerals can be used for various purposes, although it's usually better to deliver them for profit&amp;hellip; and don&amp;rsquo;t forget to watch out for those darn pirates!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Spacemaster 2120 can be played on instinct, casually or seriously. Players can deduce what minerals (and to a lesser degree, planets) have yet to appear. They can look ahead one or more moves -- &amp;quot;if I do this he will probably do that.&amp;quot; It's up to the players. You can play aggressively or peacefully. The rules set is small, there is exploration, meaningful choices, screwage, a bit of combat and some luck. A typical sequence of turns for a player might be: explore, mine, move, try to trade. Lots of &amp;quot;flow,&amp;quot; fun and replayability to be enjoyed in this light and fascinating space game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
